name: Positive control group
definition: Patient has a molecular diagnosis of IMD (positive control cohort)

name: Test cohort
definition: Patient is suspected of having an IMD based on HPO terms and/or a genomic variant of uncertain significance in a metabolic disease-associated gene (test cohort).

name: Negative control group (diseased)
definition: Genetic diagnosis that is not an IMD and without secondary metabolic dysfunction (negative control cohort)

name: Gaucher disease
definition: Gaucher disease for cohort personsalised patient management).
